OL,3,CJersey savers at 'disadvantage' over
OL,4,CUK if their bank goes bust
OL,6,FThe amount of money that an individual
OL,7,Fcan get back if their bank goes bust
OL,8,Fis being reviewed in Jersey, after a
OL,9,Fscrutiny panel suggested savers in the
OL,10,Fisland are at a "disadvantage".
OL,12,FCurrently, you can be awarded up to
OL,13,F#50,000 if you save with an
OL,14,Forganisation that becomes insolvent.
OL,16,FThat is in line with the other Crown
OL,17,FDependencies of Guernsey and the Isle
OL,18,Fof Man but significantly less than the
OL,19,FUK's #85,000 limit, with proposals
OL,20,Fthere to increase it further to
OL,21,F#110,000.
